            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This murder-mystery-idol-culture-filmmaking-documentary visual novel feels tailor made for the Nintendo Switch. While visual novels aren’t everyone’s cup of tea, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Root Film",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " has so much going on that, odds are, there’ll be something about it that appeals to you. As Rintaro Yagumo is chosen to be the director for a rebooted classic series, his dreams seem to be realised until a horrible murder takes place on set. If you’ve never played a visual novel before, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Root Film",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is a great place to start.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9X5FSjoNexI",
