          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The voice acting in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Root Film",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " was a pleasant surprise. Most of the time when dialogue is input based, it doesn’t get the privilege of being brought to life with real speech. This is yet another example of the obvious care that went into this game. One of the main recurring themes is filmmaking, and proper voice acting makes this enthusiasm for storytelling really stand out. The music doesn’t pop as much as the voices but it still goes so far as to make this game feel properly crafted as it fleshes out the aesthetic appeal.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
